{"mutation_id":"smartlist-note:claude-opus:ded68fd8-50f8-49f0-9238-f2ea98bad550","mutation_kind":"smart_list_note_created","actor_id":"claude-opus","event_time":"2026-03-25T06:54:27.662694300Z","corpus_ref":"C:\\Users\\eumin\\wkspaces\\git\\FotP\\shared-memory\\system-memory\\swarm-plans\\FotP-Bugfix-Sprint1.memory.jsonl","payload":{"kind":"smart_list_note_created","note_id":"smartlist-note:smartlistnoteclaudeopusded68fd85","title":"Simplified approach","text":"Don't use TileDealer/TilePool. Just: (1) make a SmartList of all tiles for a given color+level, (2) pick a random index, (3) remove that tile from the source list and add to the destination SmartList (the randomized stack for that bar slot). Repeat for each slot. The SmartList already handles remove. This is a 10-line function, not a class hierarchy.","bucket_paths":["smartlist/execution-plan/fotp-bugfix-sprint1/10-children/wire-tile-randomization-into-game-setup/20-observations"],"durability":"short_term"}}
