{"mutation_id":"smartlist-note:orchestrator:b1e0af93-cc2a-4a23-8ff1-ca967d386cd9","mutation_kind":"smart_list_note_created","actor_id":"orchestrator","event_time":"2026-03-25T06:57:56.812206100Z","corpus_ref":"C:\\Users\\eumin\\wkspaces\\git\\FotP\\shared-memory\\system-memory\\swarm-plans\\FotP-Bugfix-Sprint1.memory.jsonl","payload":{"kind":"smart_list_note_created","note_id":"smartlist-note:smartlistnoteorchestratorb1e0af9","title":"repair-attempt-0","text":"attempt=0, depth=0\noutcome: VERIFIED: **VERIFIED: Scarab phase fully implemented and tested**\n\n## Summary\n\nThe scarab phase implementation is complete and correct:\n\n### Implementation Evidence\n1. **GameRunner.RunScarabPhase** (lines 126-152): Fully implements player scarab usage with:\n   - Iteration through owned scarabs\n   - Player input for scarab selection\n   - Proper scarab consumption (removal before application)\n   - Effect application via Scarab.Apply()\n   - Phase transition via FinishScarabPhase()\n\n2. **TurnStateMachine.cs**:\n   - Line 97: LockDice transitions to TurnPhase.ScarabUse when remaining dice exist\n   - Lines 104-109: FinishScarabPhase() correctly transitions to ContinueDecision phase\n\n3. **Supporting Classes**: Scarab.cs, ScarabType.cs, and Player.Scarabs all exist and are properly integrated\n\n### Test Verification\n- Test `LockDice_SingleDie_TransitionsToScarabUse` (line 64-79): Validates phase transition to ScarabUse\n- Test `FinishScarabPhase_TransitionsToContinueDecision` (line 108-125): Validates phas\ncontext_observations: Bug fixes and missing features found during sprint 1 verification. All work is in src/FotP.Engine/ (pure C#, no Unity).\nReplaced the stub 'skip for now' scarab phase in GameRunner.RunTurn() with a real RunScarabPhase() method. The method loops while the player has scarabs, calls IPlayerInput.ChooseS","bucket_paths":["smartlist/execution-plan/repair-orphans/Implement scarab phase in GameRunner/40-repair-audit"],"durability":"short_term"}}
