{"mutation_id":"smartlist-note:orchestrator:4d684a44-844e-412b-a1cb-acf701bd5c12","mutation_kind":"smart_list_note_created","actor_id":"orchestrator","event_time":"2026-03-25T06:58:29.192716200Z","corpus_ref":"C:\\Users\\eumin\\wkspaces\\git\\FotP\\shared-memory\\system-memory\\swarm-plans\\FotP-Bugfix-Sprint1.memory.jsonl","payload":{"kind":"smart_list_note_created","note_id":"smartlist-note:smartlistnoteorchestrator4d684a4","title":"repair-attempt-0","text":"attempt=0, depth=0\noutcome: VERIFIED: **VERIFIED: All `IPlayerInput` decision methods are present and fully implemented**\n\nAll 10 interface methods are implemented across all three implementations:\n\n**Interface (IPlayerInput.cs:10-41):**\n1. ChooseDiceToLock\n2. ChooseContinueRolling\n3. ChooseTileToClaim\n4. ChooseDie\n5. ChooseMultipleDice\n6. ChoosePipValue\n7. ChooseScarab\n8. ChooseYesNo\n9. ChooseUseAbility\n10. ChoosePlayer\n\n**Implementations:**\n- **ConsolePlayerInput** (lines 14-134): All 10 methods ✓\n- **RandomAIInput** (lines 21-77): All 10 methods ✓\n- **ScriptedPlayerInput** (lines 29-57): All 10 methods ✓\n\nEach implementation has proper logic with sensible defaults and edge-case handling (null returns for empty lists, appropriate defaults for dice selections, etc.). The implementations are distinct and appropriate for their use cases (console prompts, random AI, deterministic testing).\ncontext_observations: CRITICAL. GameState.SetupMarket() references tiles that don't exist in TileFactory: \"Merchant\", \"Mason\", \"Architect\", \"Scholar\". These create tiles with null ClaimCriteria and no abilities. Fix by using real tile names from TileCatalog (54 tiles defined there). Either update SetupMarket to use TileC","bucket_paths":["smartlist/execution-plan/repair-orphans/Add missing IPlayerInput decision methods/40-repair-audit"],"durability":"short_term"}}
