{"mutation_id":"smartlist-note:orchestrator:c16319b6-17cf-4a46-8c83-8f6cca7ddcf8","mutation_kind":"smart_list_note_created","actor_id":"orchestrator","event_time":"2026-03-25T06:59:06.483393100Z","corpus_ref":"C:\\Users\\eumin\\wkspaces\\git\\FotP\\shared-memory\\system-memory\\swarm-plans\\FotP-Bugfix-Sprint1.memory.jsonl","payload":{"kind":"smart_list_note_created","note_id":"smartlist-note:smartlistnoteorchestratorc16319b","title":"repair-attempt-0","text":"attempt=0, depth=0\noutcome: VERIFIED: Based on my investigation, I have verified the BadOmenAbility implementation:\n\n**VERIFIED: BadOmenAbility player selection is properly implemented**\n\n## What I Found:\n\n**Core Implementation** (BadOmenAbility.cs:20-28):\n- Line 22: Filters other players with tokens > 0\n- Line 25: **Calls `player.Input.ChoosePlayer()`** to let the player select which opponent loses 1 token\n- Line 26: Falls back to `others[0]` if player returns null\n- Line 27: Decrements victim's tokens with floor of 0\n\n**Interface & All Implementations Complete:**\n- ✅ IPlayerInput.cs defines `ChoosePlayer` method (line 40)\n- ✅ ConsolePlayerInput.cs implements it (lines 123-134) - shows list with token counts\n- ✅ RandomAIInput.cs implements it (lines 73-77) - random selection\n- ✅ ScriptedPlayerInput.cs implements it (lines 56-57) - returns first for tests\n- ✅ TurnStateMachineTests.cs AutoPlayerInput implements it (lines 287-288) - first player fallback\n\n**Integration:**\n- ✅ BadOmenAbility registered in TileFactory.cs (line\ncontext_observations: BadOmenAbility passes null! to ChooseDie() as a placeholder for opponent selection, then ignores the result and targets others[0]. Fix by either (1) adding ChoosePlayer(IReadOnlyList<Player>) to IPlayerInput, or (2) since Bad Omen affects ALL other players per the rules (not a chosen one), just iter","bucket_paths":["smartlist/execution-plan/repair-orphans/Fix BadOmenAbility player selection/40-repair-audit"],"durability":"short_term"}}
